<TITLE> 'Graft can be cut by changing work method' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dinajpur, Nov 9 (bdnews24.com)--The Anticorruption Commission chairman believes graft can reduced to a great extent by changing the way the administrative work is run. "The issue of corruption is complicated. It cannot be easily done away with," Golam Rahman said at a discussion titled 'Administrative steps to resist corruption' in Dinajpur on Monday. Rahman said influential, corrupt people are slipping through the legal loopholes, but declared that no compromise would be made about the corrupt people. The ACC chief believes the efforts to usher in the digital era in Bangladesh would cut corruption. He urged everyone to be committed to resist corruption for the economic development. Dinajpur deputy commissioner Abdul Jalil, police superintendent Abu Kalam Siddique and other officials also spoke in the meeting. bdn
